title: @OspreyWSOC edged by Kennesaw State 2-1 in A-Sun Action
text: KENNESAW, Ga. â€“ A goal in the 85 th minute gave Kennesaw State the 2-1 win over the North Florida Women's Soccer Friday afternoon in conference action in Kennesaw, Ga. The Ospreys (4-10, 2-3 A-Sun) move to 2-3 in conference play and now turn their attention to USC Upstate on Sunday afternoon in Spartanburg. It was a back and forth match that saw a scoreless first half. The Ospreys best chance in the first came in the 42 nd minute, when junior took a ball into the box and fired a shot, but it was saved by the Owls keeper. Kennesaw State broke the stalemate in the 66 th minute, when Kim Fincher took a cross from Carly Pressgrove and headed it in for the 1-0 lead.
